<html><head><style>body{font-family:'Segoe UI', Calibri, sans-serif; line-height:1.6;} h1{color:#2E4053; border-bottom:2px solid #2E4053;} h2{color:#2874A6;} code{background:#F4F6F6; padding:2px; font-family:Consolas, monospace;}</style></head><body><h1>HTML Template: register.html</h1>
<h2>1. Executive Summary</h2>
<p>Defines the structural layout and content for a specific web page view.</p>
<h2>2. Code Logic &amp; Functionality</h2>
<p>Uses the Jinja2 templating engine. The file allows for dynamic data insertion using <code>{{ variable }}</code> syntax and control structures like <code>{% if %}</code> loops within standard HTML markup.</p>
<h2>3. Key Concepts &amp; Definitions</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Jinja2</strong>: A modern and designer-friendly templating language for Python.</li>
<li><strong>Template Inheritance</strong>: The ability to extend a base layout (<code>base.html</code>) to avoid code duplication.</li>
<li><strong>DOM</strong>: Document Object Model, the data representation of the objects that comprise the structure and content of a document on the web.</li>
</ul>
<h2>4. Location Details</h2>
<p><strong>Path</strong>: <code>templates\register.html</code>
<strong>Type</strong>: .HTML File</p>
<h2>5. Source Code Preview (Snippet)</h2>
<p>Running typical software analysis on this file:</p>
<p>```html
{% extends "base.html" %}</p>
<p>{% block title %}Register - School Activity Booking{% endblock %}</p>
<p>{% block content %}</p>
<div class="container py-5">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="card shadow-lg border-0">
                <div class="card-body p-5">
                    <h2 class="card-title mb-4 text-center text-primary">Create Account</h2>

                    {% if error %}
                    <div class="alert alert-danger" role="alert">
                        {{ error }}
                    </div>
                    {% endif %}

                    <form method="POST" action="{{ url_for('register') }}" id="registerForm">
                        <input type="hidden" name="csrf_token" value="{{ csrf_token() }}">
                        <div class="mb-3">
                            <label for="name" class="form-label">Full Name *</label>
                            <input type="text" class="form-control form-control-lg" id="name" name="full_name" required>
                        </div>

                        <div class="mb-3">
                            <label for="email" class="form-label">Email Address *</label>
                            <input type="email" class="form-control form-control-lg" id="email" name="email" required>
                        </div>

                        <div class="mb-3">
                            <label for="phone" class="form-label">Phone Number *</label>
                            <input type="tel" class="form-control form-control-lg" id="phone" name="phone"
                                pattern="[0-9+\s-]{10,15}"
                                title="Phone number must contain only digits, spaces, or hyphens (10-15 characters)"
                                required>
                        </div>

                        <div class="mb-3">
                            <label for="password" class="form-label">Password *</label>
                            <input type="password" class="form-control form-control-lg" id="password" name="password"
                                minlength="8" required>
                            <small class="text-muted">At least 8 characters required</small>
                        </div>

                        <div class="mb-4">
                            <label for="confirm_password" class="form-label">Confirm Password *</label>
                            <input type="password" class="form-control form-control-lg" id="confirm_password"
                                name="confirm_password" required>
                        </div>

                        <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary-custom btn-lg w-100 mb-3">Register</button>
                    </form>

                    <p class="text-center text-muted">
                        Already have an account? <a href="{{ url_for('login') }}" class="text-decoration-none">Login
                            here</a>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<p>{% endblock %}
```</p></body></html>